# Capstone: Component Library

Package your learning into a real, documented, variant-driven component library — the kind a team
could install and depend on. This is Module 7's project grown up into a governed, distributable
system.

<ProjectBrief
	title="Build and document a component library"
	time="3–5 hours"
	goal="Build ~10 typed, accessible, variant-driven Svelte 5 components on a shared token + cn() foundation, with a barrel export, a docs/gallery page rendering every variant, and tests — packaged for reuse."
	requirements={[
		'A token foundation (semantic CSS variables) + shared cn() utility',
		'At least 10 components: Button, IconButton, Badge, Card, Alert, Input, Select, Checkbox, Modal, Tabs',
		'Typed orthogonal variant props; every component accepts a `class` override via cn()',
		'Accessibility built in: roles, labels, focus management, keyboard support',
		'A barrel export (index.ts) and a living docs/gallery page',
		'Component tests querying by role/name; CI running lint/check/test/build'
	]}
	stretch={[
		'Publish as a private npm package consumed by a second app',
		'Add a dark-mode and a second-brand story to the gallery',
		'Generate the token table in docs from the token source'
	]}
/>

## The gallery is the product

A component library *is* its documentation. Ship a page that renders every component in every variant —
it's how consumers discover, compare, and copy.

